			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Tarlang fight in Nobles Causeway Advice Please<a name="68956"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Nov 4 04 8:59 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Howdy folks!
<br />

<br />
Wiladancer from Torv here with another newb question.
<br />

<br />
I have a friend, Zebsis, who is shooting for his Necro Epic 1.5 and this requires a lil fight with Tarlang, a level 73 Kiv in Nobles Causeway. 
<br />

<br />
This is taking place this Friday night at 9:00PM. I think Zebsis has a total of 3-Bards at the moment, myself included. My thoughts are, the more the merrier, so if any Bard 60-70 is bored and wishes for a challenge, please join us and bring some friends. My desire is to have 1-Bard per group and there will be 8-10 groups, so that leaves us 5-7 short. So come on folks, let's rock the joint. I personally haven't even been to Nobles Causeway yet.
<br />

<br />
There were 40 level 65+ folks on his last attempt and they didn't make it. 
<br />

<br />
I have jotted down some thoughts on this and would appreciate any advice or corrections based upon what I have written. I am only level 65 and have Epic 1.0 (thanks to my many friends including Zeb). 
<br />

<br />

<br />
Post from Fate's Presence Site:
<br />

<br />
Come one, Come all. Friday Night at 9:00-9:30PM EST join me (if I'm home on time) and all our friends in helping one very deserving, and helluva good Necromancer ZEBSIS from Northstar Legion. Yes, the very place where our whacky friend Buddhafist, the walking Bard hurdle, resides. 
<br />

<br />
Here's a lil something on the fight: 
<br />

<br />
Here is the complete Necro walkthrough: 
<br />

<br />
http://necro.mylostfantasy.com/Soulwhisper.html 
<br />

<br />
I believe Zeb is going after Tarlang on the Nobles Causeway. 
<br />

<br />
http://eqbeastiary.allakhazam.com/search.shtml?id=16467 
<br />

<br />
This sounds like one real tough cookie. Quads for over 3k EACH 
<br />

<br />
Has an AoE Slow/DoT for melee and casters alike POISON BASED 
<br />

<br />
&quot;As of the patch on September 16, Tarlang rampages and flurries. Be aware of these new, and potentualy deadly, ability. If he agroes you first when you spawn him, you will be the rampage tank, so make sure at least two people tag him and you feign death to loose rampage.&quot; 
<br />

<br />
Wila's Recommendation from a Bard Perspective: 
<br />

<br />
1) Get Everyone possible a Rune/Damage Shield 
<br />

<br />
2) Have one Bard per group sing DA right before Hail. His AoE goes off upon spawning Red to 70 (I think). 
<br />

<br />
3) Necro Feigns or Tank drops DA song, or both to scure aggro off of Zebsis 
<br />

<br />
4) CH cycle begins. Alla's calls for a 5-Cleric Chain 
<br />

<br />
5) Each Bard Twists in Psalm of Veeshan to Max all resists. Poison Resist is Key with this guy. 
<br />

<br />
6) Next Highest Bard, using Puretone and Amplification, sings Harmony of Sound to Debuff 
<br />

<br />
7) If a Third Bard is Present, each bard choose a DoT which contain serious debuffs 
<br />

<br />
 All Bards twisting in Call of the Muse for Overhaste/15% Foci 
<br />

<br />
9) All Bards have memmed Aria of Asceticism for removing the following, focusing first on healers then on tanks, et al (hotkeys set in advance) 
<br />

<br />
Caustic Atmosphere 
<br />
Classes: None 
<br />
Description: 
<br />
1: Decrease Spell Haste by 25% 
<br />
2: Decrease Attack Speed by 25% 
<br />
3: Decrease HP when cast by 550 
<br />
4: Limit: Combat Skills Not Allowed 
<br />

<br />
Alla's states that this is a 10-minute fight as well, as this guy has a ton of HP. 
<br />

<br />
Please email me at kfs28@yahoo.com or kstahl10@comcast.net and YahooIM me as captain_kurt M-F, 8AM-5PM. I will attempt to recruit a few more folks from the day. 
<br />

<br />
Sounds like a blast. Hopefully I'll be in time to see it Friday night. 
<br />

<br />
RAR 
<br />

<br />
Wila..... 
<br />

<br />
end post...
<br />

<br />
Thanks in advance to all te folks here at EqDiva. You all rock.
<br />

<br />
Wiladancer Abiff - 65th Newb Extraordinaire from Torv</span></td>
