			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Tarlang fight in Nobles Causeway Advice Please<a name="70559"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Dec 2 04 9:07 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>1) Get Everyone possible a Rune/Damage Shield 
<br />

<br />
IMO, runes are fairly useless in the high end game.  The bad part of his aoe isn't the damage, it's the effects.  So 200 or 300 or whatever won't really save the raid.  DS is only important for tanks.
<br />

<br />
2) Have one Bard per group sing DA right before Hail. His AoE goes off upon spawning Red to 70 (I think). 
<br />

<br />
Good plan <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" /> 
<br />

<br />
3) Necro Feigns or Tank drops DA song, or both to scure aggro off of Zebsis 
<br />

<br />
Good plan <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" /> .  Don't forget to /disc or a healer or something.
<br />

<br />
4) CH cycle begins. Alla's calls for a 5-Cleric Chain 
<br />

<br />
Personally, CH rotations don't really work well for these mobs with insane dps.  Let's say you have a 15k tank (there are a fair number out now a days) from your resident uber-guild.  In 10 seconds, 7.5k gets healed.  If he's on the lower end of life, BAM, he's at 50%.... Not too efficient. 
<br />

<br />
If they all spam heal, every couple of seconds he gets a nice infusion of several k hp.  This is important.  And a crit on a spam heal can be for 8k.  Suddenly, a 1.8 second heal recovers more hp than a 10 second ch.  
<br />

<br />
5) Each Bard Twists in Psalm of Veeshan to Max all resists. Poison Resist is Key with this guy. 
<br />

<br />
If you have that many, I highly doubt you'll get that many bards<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />.  Put all the important people in 2 groups (MT + some healers, and then some more healers + main dps) and the other one sings ae resists.  All should have ae loaded for back up.
<br />

<br />
6) Next Highest Bard, using Puretone and Amplification, sings Harmony of Sound to Debuff 
<br />

<br />
Pure Tone and Amp on HoS = nadda.  Biggest drum gets HoS. These days one can BUY a drum that is better than Puretone without AA's.  3.8 mod can be gotten for a drum in baz + SM4 + 1 bought cap raiser.  Get biggest drum to HoS and first AE resister<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />.
<br />

<br />

<br />
7) If a Third Bard is Present, each bard choose a DoT which contain serious debuffs 
<br />

<br />
I personally would be more concerned with MT bard (AC song + war march for ds + pov), healer / dps bard, and ae bard (hos + ae saves + ae mana is generally a good idea).  Don't need every one to sing the overhaste and foci, unless you have like 7+.
<br />

<br />
A fourth bard would be ideal for more dps (war march of muram can add like 100 atk, + over haste, + pov).  Stack the groups with that in mind.
<br />

<br />
Also, put the SA and maybe even TA with the MA for MT barding.
<br />

<br />
9) All Bards have memmed Aria of Asceticism for removing the following, focusing first on healers then on tanks, et al (hotkeys set in advance) 
<br />

<br />
Good idea in theory, but essential bards (ie MT bard, ae bard, etc.) may have a bit of a hard time dropping things to heal. 
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
Not to flame or anything, but my raid experience seems to have different milage than yours.  I see you thinking about stuff, which is awesome and a hallmark of a good bard, but the best milage for bards is concentrating what needs to be done<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />.  As an example, say you need 6 adds that need to be taken care of.  You could A) devote 1 enc to mezz them, B) devote 2 bards *that need to know each other decently well* to mez them, or C) get 1 bard / other kite class to kite them.  Even if they summon, just getting agro (ie; they spawn in a different room) and running circles can get the job done.
<br />

<br />
AE resists with a good drum and the aa's can add like 180.  Assuming the ae isn't too hard to resist (-300 for the avg joy should be fine with buffs + gear + ae song.  -400 is tricky and needs some PoV loving.  -500 is gonna need time gear to reliably resist, and anything over -900 is unresistable<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-4.gif" border="0" alt="Tongue out" hspace="2" />).
<br />

<br />
Puretone will actually decrease the drum mods available now a days, btw.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
