				<td colspan="2"><span>Thanks for the info. 
<br />

<br />
You are certainly correct as far as Raid mileage. I have very little, being a father of a 1 and a half year old and 3 and a half year old and a Tovonnite for 4 and a half years. 
<br />

<br />
No worries about flaming me. I don't consider it as such. I find that listening to the &quot;pros&quot; here at eqDiva are the only means of preventing costly mistakes at the expense of other peoples' time. I, in turn, thank you for a complete review and critique of my wishful thinking. That takes time and I appreciate your sharing.
<br />

<br />
I do enjoy strategizing and planning using Reeds worksheet and tidbits picked up from eqDiva. By planning and discussing strategy I have found that 90% of my Raids are successful and fun. I love learning how to better master my character and while I will never see EP or Time, I'd like to think I provide the best twist for my group whenever possible.
<br />

<br />
As far as a bard per group, I have never been on a Raid with more than 4 bards. So I may have a better chance with the Mega-Millions Quick-Pick. 
<br />

<br />
It does appear as though the raid has been delayed for a while due to the exodus of folks to EQ2 and WoW.
<br />

<br />
My current guild consists of about 10 people with 3-4 alts each. When asked to gather together for any one of our needs, we usually have at least one solid tight-knit group and then ask our friends to help. 
<br />
The friend I wish to assist is in a guild of over 200 people, but, as I shook my head in dismay, only 30 of his guildmates were actually present to help him. In my opinion, that isn't right, but as my wife states &quot;when did your opinion actually have any bearing?&quot;
<br />

<br />
I know we will have 3-4 bards in our next attempt, so I will pass along this information to them. 
<br />

<br />
Thank you for posting and I will let you know the outcome, when and if we do this.
<br />

<br />
Rock on!
<br />

